The paper proposes reinforcement learning algorithms for optimizing the performance of dynamic multimedia systems, which involves cross-layer optimization and real-time delay constraints. This suggests that the paper could belong to several arXiv CS sub-categories, including Machine Learning (cs.LG), Multimedia (cs.MM), Systems and Control (cs.SY), Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI), and Information Theory (cs.IT). Among these, Machine Learning and Multimedia are the most likely categories, as the paper focuses on developing learning algorithms for multimedia systems. Systems and Control and Artificial Intelligence are also relevant, as the paper deals with optimizing the performance of a dynamic system, while Information Theory could be relevant for analyzing the communication overheads of the proposed algorithms.
